<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-89-0186 </DOCNO><TEXT>The authors conduct a broad review of the aspects of automation implementedin a wide range of microelement analytical techniques and equipment,including spectroscopy, chromatography, extraction, sorption, electrochemistry,luminescence, and radiochemistry. Materials discussed for analysis includetoxic and radioactive components, pollutants, metals, and organic compounds.Some data are tabulated.</TEXT></DOC>